		 <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
         <p style="margin-bottom:50px; text-align:center; font-size: 18px; color: #333333; margin-top: 20px;  line-height: 1.5;">At Job Delta, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users' personal information. This privacy policy outlines the types of personal information we collect, how we use it, and how we keep it safe.</p>

		<section class="news-item">
        <h2>Personal Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>When you sign up for an account on Job Delta, we collect your name, email address, and password. We may also collect additional information such as your location, skills, and work experience. This information is used to create your profile and to match you with relevant job opportunities.</p>
		</section>

		<section class="news-item">
		<h2>How We Use Your Personal Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal information to provide you with a personalized experience on Job Delta. This includes matching you with relevant job opportunities, sending you job alerts and other notifications, and providing customer support. We may also use your personal information to improve the Job Delta platform and to develop new features and services.</p>
		</section>
	   
	    <section class="news-item">
		<h2>How We Keep Your Personal Information Safe</h2>
        <p>We take the security of your personal information seriously and have implemented a variety of measures to keep it safe. This includes using encryption to protect your data in transit, storing your data on secure servers, and regularly monitoring our systems for unauthorized access or suspicious activity.</p>
		</section>

	    <section class="news-item">
	    <h2>Sharing Your Personal Information</h2>
        <p>We may share your personal information with third-party service providers who assist us with providing the Job Delta platform and its related services. We may also share your information with potential employers who are interested in hiring you for a job opportunity. However, we will not sell, rent, or otherwise disclose your personal information to third parties for their own marketing purposes.</p>
		</section>

	    <section class="news-item">
		<h2>Your Choices and Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to access, modify, or delete your personal information at any time. You can do this by logging into your Job Delta account and editing your profile. You may also choose to opt-out of receiving job alerts and other notifications by updating your account settings. If you have any questions or concerns about your personal information, please contact us at privacy@jobdelta.com.</p
		</section>

	    <section class="news-item">
		<h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our business practices or legal requirements. If we make any material changes to the policy, we will notify you by email or by posting a notice on the Job Delta platform.</p>
		</section>

	    <section class="news-item">
		<a href="ContactUs.aspx" style="text-decoration:none; color:inherit";>
		<h2>Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or our privacy practices, please contact us at privacy@jobdelta.com.</p>
